//Our team is working with N. Virginia & they have some Important data. We want same data in another region// -- 

-> Fire an EC2 Instance(dev-server) : 10Gib gp2
__________________________
->Elastic Block Store Menu
___________________________
 -: Volume - name(root-vol) - gp2 10Gib
> create volume -: name(data-vol) - gp2 5Gib

->Action ->Attach Volume ->Select Instance

->Open the terminal using ssh
#df -h
#mkdir /data
#lsblk
#mkfs.ext4 /dev/nvme1n1
#mount /dev/nvme1n1 /data/
#cd /data
#touch pooja.txt{1..100}

___________________________
Create snapshot (Of Disk)
________________________

-> in AWS site go to Elastic Block Store select Snapshots
-> select volume
-> launch/create
-> Select snapshot

->Create duplicate session
->Change the region to Ohio

->Go to N. Verginia EC2 page
->Go to Snapshot Menu then select the snapshot->action->copy option->then select destination as Ohio

->Go to Ohio EC2 page

->Fire an EC2 instance

-> snapshot menu
-> Select snapshot
-> Create Volume From Snapshot
-> select zone
-> Go to volumes
-> New Volume would be present as available
-> select that volume click action
-> attach volume

#df -h
#lsblk
#mkdir /Prod-data-ohio
#mount /dev/nvme1n1 /Prod-data-ohio
#cd /Prod-data-ohio/
#ll

